         <abstract>
            <p>The nonlinear stability in the L&lt;sup&gt;p&lt;/sup&gt;-norm, p ≥ 1, of stationary weak discrete shocks for the Lax-Friedrichs scheme approximating general m × m systems of nonlinear hyperbolic conservation laws is proved, provided that the summations of the initial perturbations equal zero. The result is proved by using both a weighted estimate and characteristic energy method based on the internal structures of the discrete shocks and the essential monotonicity of the Lax-Friedrichs scheme.</p>
          </abstract>
